He stresses the importance of checking the presence of bats before proceeding with the maintenance of the properties, because by destroying without wanting a single nest of motherhood, one can thus cause the death of 400 females and small ones, or even the disappearance of an entire local population.
The bats are protected and it is illegal to kill them, disturb them, or destroy their perch.
