Syria 'prepared' for return of refugees, according to Foreign Minister
Syria says it is ready for the voluntary return of refugees and calls for help to rebuild this country devastated by a war that has lasted for more than seven years.
Addressing the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem said the situation in the country was improving.
“Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
The government is continuing to rehabilitate areas destroyed by terrorists in order to restore normality.
All conditions are now met for the voluntary repatriation of refugees to the country they have been forced to leave due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures aimed at their daily lives and livelihoods.
The United Nations estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have deserted the country since the start of the war in 2011.
Six more million people still living in the country need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian regime would welcome aid in the reconstruction of this devastated country.
He stressed, however, that he would not accept conditional aid or aid from countries sponsoring the insurrection.
Europe wins the Ryder Cup in Paris
The European team won the 2018 Ryder Cup by beating the U.S. team with a final score of 16.5 to 10.5 at Golf National near Paris, France.
The United States has now lost six consecutive times on European soil and has not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe regained the title when Danish captain Thomas Bjorn’s team crossed the 14.5 points needed to beat the United States.
American star Phil Mickelson, who found himself in trouble during most of the tournament, pushed his start in the water at the 16th hole in par-3, giving his duel to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari excelled in all his rounds, becoming one of the four players to have ever reached 5-0-0 since the current format of the tournament, whose first edition dates back to 1979.
American Jordan Spieth was dismissed 5-4 by the least-placed player of the European team, Thorbjorn Olesen, from Denmark.
The best golfer in the world, Dustin Johnson, bowed 2 and 1 against Englishman Ian Poulter, who could have played his last Ryder Cup.
A veteran of eight Ryder Cups, Spanish Sergio Garcia became the all-time European champion with a total of 25.5 career points.
